44 SECTION 9. Section 44, chapter 599, Oregon Laws 2023, as amended by section 5, chapter 104,
45 Oregon Laws 2024, is amended to read:
[13]

A-Eng. SB 5701
1 Sec. 44. (1) For the biennium beginning July 1, 2023, at the request of the Oregon Department
2 of Administrative Services, after the department consults with the Oregon Business Development
3 Department, the State Treasurer is authorized to issue lottery bonds pursuant to ORS 286A.560 to
4 286A.585 in an amount that produces $20 million in net proceeds for the purposes described in sub-
5 section (2) of this section, plus an additional amount estimated by the State Treasurer to be neces-
6 sary to pay bond-related costs.
7 (2) Net proceeds of lottery bonds issued under this section must be transferred to the Oregon
8 Business Development Department for deposit in the [Coos Bay Channel Fund established by section
9 15, chapter 746, Oregon Laws 2007, for distribution to the Oregon International Port of Coos Bay to
10 deepen and widen the Coos Bay Federal Navigation Channel and for the design, engineering, permit-
11 ting and land acquisition efforts related to the Pacific Coast Intermodal Port project] OBDD Eco-
12 nomic Development Distributions Fund established under section 28, chapter 748, Oregon
13 Laws 2017, for distribution to the Urban Flood Safety and Water Quality District for levee
14 system improvements along the Columbia River from Sauvie Island to the Sandy River in
15 Troutdale.
16 (3) The Legislative Assembly finds that the use of lottery bond proceeds will create jobs, further
17 economic development, finance public education or restore and protect parks, beaches, watersheds
18 and native fish and wildlife, and is authorized based on the [finding that port facilities and related
19 infrastructure are an integral part of the commercial and industrial infrastructure of this state, and
